TY  - JOUR
TI  - Efficiency in the Optimum Supply of Public Goods
AU  - Lau, Lawrence J.
AU  - Sheshinski, Eytan
AU  - Stiglitz, Joseph E.
AB  - [In this paper we are concerned with the following question: in any economy with several public goods, what are the conditions under which the conventional optimality rule of equality between the sum of marginal rates of substitution and the marginal rate of transformation still holds even in the presence of distortionary taxation? Two cases are considered. In the first case, the taxes may be arbitrary. In the second case, the taxes are optimally chosen.]
C1  - Full publication date: Mar., 1978
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1913900
